				<td colspan="2"><span>I play 2 characters. My main is a lvl 54 bard (def 194) and my second is a 42 beastlord (def 208). 
<br />
The bards gear is better than the bst's, but the bst can tank almost as well. i.e. fighting sea-fury cyclops, both self buffed, and singing apropriat melee songs my bard usually ends a fight between 20 - 40% health on db mobs. The bst about 10 - 30% hp on the same ones (white to him).
<br />
There is a 12 level difference here, what gives.
<br />
I know bards are not tank classes, and we have a lot more options to kill mobs, but I was trying to raise parry at the time. I was just a little surprised to see this. Does the 14 pt difference in def make such a big jump in damage taken.
<br />

<br />
Tuber lvl 54.11</span></td>
